    {
      "name": "3. Messagerie (REST endpoints)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Conversation History (from User 1 to User 2)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{jwt_token_1}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:3000/messages/history/2",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "3000",
              "path": ["messages", "history", "2"]
            },
            "description": "Fetch the full history of conversation using jwt_token_1."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Websocket Guidelines (Read Description)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "HOW TO TEST SOCKET.IO",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:3000/",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "3000",
              "path": [""]
            },
            "description": "### Postman Socket.IO Testing Guide:\n\n1. In Postman, click **New > Socket.IO** to open a true WebSocket tab.\n2. URL: `ws://localhost:3000/chat`\n3. Go to the **Headers** tab.\n   - Key: `Authorization`\n   - Value: `Bearer {{jwt_token_1}}` (or `{{jwt_token_2}}` for the other user).\n4. Click **Connect**.\n\n---\n\n#### EVENTS TO EMIT (in the 'Events' pane at the bottom):\n\n**1. Register (Required first step!)**\n- Event Name: `register`\n- Message type: JSON\n- Body: `{}`\n\n**2. Send a regular message**\n- Event Name: `sendMessage`\n- Message type: JSON\n- Body: \n```json\n{\n  \"receiverId\": 2,\n  \"content\": \"Hello User 2!\"\n}\n```\n\n**3. Send a reply message**\n- Event Name: `sendMessage`\n- Message type: JSON\n- Body: \n```json\n{\n  \"receiverId\": 2,\n  \"content\": \"This is my reply to your message.\",\n  \"replyToId\": 1\n}\n```\n\n**4. React to a message**\n- Event Name: `reactToMessage`\n- Message type: JSON\n- Body: \n```json\n{\n  \"messageId\": 1,\n  \"emoji\": \"🔥\"\n}\n```"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
